{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "b1b29b5a-e9dd-4b47-8204-53c365709c3e",
    "name": "Sales Targets API",
    "description": "Target-related Postman collection extracted from the real Laravel backend after the team-based target flow update.\n\n**Seeded demo (default emails):** leader `sales.leader@rakez.com`, marketer `sales@rakez.com`, password `password`. Run `php artisan db:seed` and `SalesLeaderTeamProjectsLinkSeeder` is in the default pipeline so team projects are non-empty.\n\n**Collection variable `strict_seed_assertions`:** `true` (default) asserts team projects total >= 1 and stricter checks. Set to `false` if testing against an empty DB.\n\nAuth:\n- POST /api/login\n- GET /api/user\n- POST /api/logout\n\nCore target APIs:\n- GET /api/sales/targets/my\n- GET /api/sales/targets/by-project/{contractId}\n- POST /api/sales/targets\n- PATCH /api/sales/targets/{id}\n\nTeam-based source of truth for leader target setup:\n- GET /api/sales/team/projects\n- GET /api/sales/team/members\n- GET /api/sales/projects/{contractId}/units\n\nCurrent backend behavior:\n- Sales leader sees only completed projects linked to the leader team by project management via contract_team.\n- Sales leader can create a target only for a sales marketer in the same team.\n- Target can be project-level or unit-level.\n- Sales marketer sees only targets assigned to them personally.\n- Leader view of /api/sales/targets/my returns project cards (item_type = project_assignment) sourced from PM team linkage, not sales_project_assignments.\n\nSuggested order:\n1. Login - Sales Leader\n2. Get Team Projects\n3. Get Team Members\n4. Get Project Units\n5. Create Target\n6. Get Targets By Project - Leader\n7. Login - Sales Marketer\n8. Get My Targets - Marketer View\n9. Update Target Status",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
